    "discriminators": [
     "Chain jingle is one of the most distinctive textures in UCS: a VERY dense train of tiny bright metallic onsets (the highest onset_rate_per_second of any metal class, transient_count in the tens), each with a short inharmonic ring, and IRREGULAR - onset_periodicity stays low even when the chain is dragged steadily.",
     "Almost no low_band_energy: links are small and stiff. That, plus onset density, is the boundary against METAL-MOVEMENT (fewer, bigger, lower onsets) and METAL-CRASH & DEBRIS (loud, destructive, front-weighted).",
     "Against CHAINS-IMPACT: MOVEMENT is a sustained jingle bed with no dominant transient; IMPACT is one big hit or a taut snap."
    ],
